18/07/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The VMRO-DPMNE and the Democratic Party of Albanians (DPA) reportedly have reached agreement on forming a new government. 
After the leaders of the two parties met on Monday (17 July), both Antonio Milososki of VMRO-DPMNE and Arben Xhaferri of the DPA confirmed that an agreement in principle had been reached. 
The coalition, also compromising the National Social Democratic Party, Democratic Development of Macedonia and the Party for European Future, would have a comfortable majority in parliament. 
(Vecer, MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 18/07/06; A1 TV - 17/07/06)
